				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Shouldn't be... PAL PPUs has 341 pixels per scanline and 5 master clock cycles per pixel, for 1705 master clock cycles per scanline, or 284+1/6 chroma periods per scanline. Multiply by 312 scanlines to get 88660 (exactly) chroma periods per field, so the output from the 2C07 should be identical from refresh to refresh ... unlike on the 2C02 where it alternates every other field.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

